latestIgtvVideos.title: TRENDING COFFEE 2☕😃
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Dalgona Coffee Recipe, a trending viral recipe from tik tok. This is super easy to make and taste absolutely delicious.
.
Ingredients
Instant Coffee - 2 tblsp
Sugar - 4 tblsp or more
Hot Water - 2 tblsp
Cold Milk - as needed
Ice Cubes as needed
Sweetener for milk if needed

STEPS
Take coffee, sugar, hot water in a bowl. Mix well.

Use a hand blender to whip this till it gets light and fluffy. It will take around 3 to 5 mins.

Now take a serving glass. Fill with ice. Add in sweetened milk.

Top with the whipped coffee. Stick and straw in and serve.

Mix well and enjoy this  hehehehehe 😅
.

latestPosts.caption:
This Pandharpur Wari Pilgrimage / Ashadhi Wari means A Palkhi sohala from Alandi to Pandharpur is Treat to your 5 Sensory Organs, and that’s What this video is about !! 
I have been experiencing it for the last 11 years, except for those 2  years of covid - 19. So after the Pandemic, this year’s Palkhi Sohala was Very Special. 
12 Lakh Warkaris were walking on that mighty Dive ghat Road; Chanting, plying Pakhawaj, and Singing bhajans with those saffron flags in hand, marching towards Vishnu reincarnated Lord Vitthala Mandir. 
The sun shone brilliantly in the blue sky with Dark rainy clouds drifting across the western ghats which were making Perfect light exposure for shooting Videos and Photos. 
.

Funfacts:
UNESCO World Heritage Site for its cultural and architectural significance 🙌🏻

Some believe its precision is so advanced, aliens 👽 might have built it — but historians say NO, it was the work of our own ancient Indian craftsmanship 😎

Entirely carved from a single basalt rock, and that too top-down, not built bottom-up 🤯
Built by 🤴 King Krishna I of the Rashtrakuta dynasty in the 8th century CE

#incredibleindia #kailasatemple #elloracaves 
[ UNESCO world heritage site, Rockcur architecture, Sambhaji Nagar, caves, ramayan carvings, basalt rock]

A Marvel Carved from a Single Basalt Rock!
📍 Ellora Caves, Sambhaji Nagar

Built in the 8th century by King Krishna I of the Rashtrakuta dynasty

It’s said that over 200,000 tons of rock were excavated to build this, and it took nearly 20 years of non-stop work. Even today, archaeologists are amazed at how it was constructed without modern tools.

Fireflies season started in Maharashtra ✨⛰️

After trekking through the mighty Sandhan Valley, we ended the day with one of nature’s most magical shows — thousands of fireflies lighting up the night near Bhandardara! 🌠

Location: Purushwadi / Samrad / Rajur villages (near Bhandardara, Maharashtra)

Best Time: Late May to early June (just before monsoon)

Stay Options:
	•	Local village homestays (affordable + authentic!)
	•	Firefly camping with meals & guided night trails – search for camps near Samrad or Purushwadi
	•	Bhandardara lakeside resorts for a comfy stay with views 

Tips:
	•	Book stays in advance – firefly season is short & popular
	•	Carry a torch (red light preferred to not disturb fireflies)
	•	Don’t use flash photography – enjoy the view with your eyes!
